              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The tritium gas chamber was used to produce",
                "neutrons by the bombardment with the deuteron beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural uranium metal disks of 1.6 cm diameter X 0.05",
                "cm thickness with an average weight of about 1.5 g,",
                "packed in 0.2 mm thickness pure aluminium foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A HPGe-92X Spectrum Master of gamma-",
                "spectrometer. The resolution of the 120 cm3 HPGe",
                "detector was 1.85 keV (FWHM) for the 1.33 MeV gamma",
                "ray of Co-60."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The sample sandwiched between two",
                "standardized thin samples was mounted in a double",
                "fission chamber, which covered with Cd of 1 mm",
                "thickness. The efficiency of the fission chamber was",
                "checked by 197Au(n,g) 198Au reaction with thermal",
                "neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight technique was used to measure",
                "the neutron spectrum."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission product activities were measured by",
                "HPGe gamma-ray spectrometry. Four samples were",
                "irradiated for a period varying from 0.5 to 30 h at a",
                "distance of about 5 cm from the neutron source in the",
                "direction of zero degree."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ABSFY"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission rate was monitored by fission chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
